{"id":5344,"date":"2026-04-14T19:59:28","date_gmt":"2026-04-14T14:29:28","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/?page_id=5344"},"modified":"2026-04-14T20:01:33","modified_gmt":"2026-04-14T14:31:33","slug":"taking-shelter-of-gurus-lotus-feet-ultimately-means-following-his-instructions","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/festivals\/2026\/hhgkg-triobhav\/","title":{"rendered":"Taking shelter of Guru\u2019s lotus feet\u00a0ultimately means\u00a0following His instructions!\u00a0"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"Taking shelter of Guru\u2019s lotus feet ultimately means following His instructions!\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/Bb1m3JsfygY?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>HH Gopal Krishna Maharaj&nbsp;Triobhav&nbsp;Utsav| HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj | April 14, 2026<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">This is the second celebration of the disappearance of Gopal&nbsp;Krishna&nbsp;Maharaj. As everyone is aware, he has played&nbsp;a very important&nbsp;role in the expansion of ISKCON in India.&nbsp;In fact, we see that the whole of Delhi, which is a huge city, is covered with about 18 temples, all due to the inspiration of Gopal&nbsp;Krishna&nbsp;Maharaj.&nbsp;And of course, he has also been preaching and managing in Maharashtra, Mumbai and in Gujarat as well.&nbsp;If we examine his words&nbsp;and&nbsp;instructions, we see that primarily he wanted people to simply follow the instructions of Srila&nbsp;Prabhupad.&nbsp;In fact, he kept instructions&nbsp;very simple. And this is also the lesson we learn from&nbsp;all of&nbsp;our Acharyas.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;everyday&nbsp;we do Srila&nbsp;Prabhupad&#8217;s&nbsp;Guru Puja.&nbsp;And we pray there that the feet of Guru are the ultimate shelter.&nbsp;And by taking shelter of those feet, we get perfection in devotional service.&nbsp;This is not a new&nbsp;concept,&nbsp;it is being&nbsp;stated&nbsp;in the Upanishads.&nbsp;Of course, it is not simply a statement about Bhakti, it is a statement for all types of knowledge conveyed through the Vedic literature.&nbsp;And what that means, apart from the poetic expression of taking shelter of lotus feet, it&nbsp;actually means&nbsp;that we are willing to follow the instructions.&nbsp;So&nbsp;you can&nbsp;literally touch&nbsp;the&nbsp;feet or roll on the dust of the feet of the Acharya,&nbsp;but that is not enough.&nbsp;Certainly, it is beneficial for us. But taking shelter of the lotus feet&nbsp;ultimately means&nbsp;following instructions.&nbsp;So, you can take the foot dust forever, but you&nbsp;don&#8217;t&nbsp;follow the instructions, that means nothing. And, if you&nbsp;don&#8217;t&nbsp;take the foot dust, but&nbsp;you follow the instructions, that is everything.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, Srila&nbsp;Prabhupad&nbsp;in one of his&nbsp;vyasya&nbsp;puja offerings to&nbsp;Bhaktisiddhanta&nbsp;Saraswati&nbsp;Thakur after his disappearance, was writing that, what is the use of offering all these fruits and flowers? And what he meant by that is&nbsp;that,&nbsp;the followers of&nbsp;Bhaktisiddhanta&nbsp;Saraswati&nbsp;Thakur were worshipping him physically, but they were not following his instructions.&nbsp;Instead of expanding one movement, they divided it into many parts. So then, what was the use of the worship?&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Srila&nbsp;Prabhupad&nbsp;gave many instructions. And of course, he&nbsp;didn&#8217;t&nbsp;want us to deviate from the scriptures.&nbsp;And therefore, he gave many books like Bhagavad Gita and&nbsp;Srimad&nbsp;Bhagavatam. So, in that way, those instructions are without any dispute.&nbsp;But,&nbsp;one of his primary other instructions was to keep ISKCON unified.&nbsp;So, he gives the example of a group of sticks. And if you take a stick, you can break it. If you have a group of sticks, you cannot break it.&nbsp;So ISKCON, as one unified movement, is strong, when it divides up, then it becomes weak.&nbsp;So&nbsp;this was one of&nbsp;Prabhupad&#8217;s&nbsp;main instructions.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">And as I mentioned, Gopal&nbsp;Krishna&nbsp;Maharaj emphasized this a lot. What does that mean in practical terms? We will see&nbsp;that,&nbsp;there are reasons for dividing. People have different opinions.&nbsp;People may be possessive of a certain temple. So, unity means,&nbsp;we&nbsp;have to&nbsp;give up&nbsp;all of&nbsp;these separate endeavours. We&nbsp;have to&nbsp;give up our individual goals in pursuance of the common goal.&nbsp;We&nbsp;have to&nbsp;sacrifice individual opinions for the common opinion. That is sometimes a challenge. Everybody still has their individual identity and their individual ideas.&nbsp;But,&nbsp;the whole point of devotional service is,&nbsp;we are willing to sacrifice all of&nbsp;that. So, when we say, take shelter of the lotus feet of Guru, taking shelter means we give up self-interest.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">There is also another unfortunate phenomenon.&nbsp;Disciples are very devoted to&nbsp;Guru,&nbsp;because&nbsp;you&nbsp;should&nbsp;surrender to the lotus feet of Guru.&nbsp;But,&nbsp;they become so devoted,&nbsp;that they cannot surrender to anybody else. They cannot surrender to a higher authority.&nbsp;They cannot even surrender to Srila&nbsp;Prabhupad. So, though there is devotion to Guru, we also&nbsp;have to&nbsp;see the general structure of our society.&nbsp;And ultimately, the&nbsp;final surrender is to Srila&nbsp;Prabhupad.&nbsp;And it is for that purpose,&nbsp;that every day we do Guru Puja to Srila&nbsp;Prabhupad.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">And as I said, Gopal Krishna&nbsp;Maharaj always emphasized that one should be devoted to following&nbsp;Prabhupad&#8217;s&nbsp;instruction and keep&nbsp;the society together. So, in commemorating Gopal Krishna&nbsp;Maharaj, then&nbsp;in expressing your devotion, you should understand that your primary goal is to follow that instruction.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, in&nbsp;Guruvastakam&nbsp;it says, if you satisfy Guru, then everything is successful. So,&nbsp;if as disciples you can think of ways to&nbsp;fulfill&nbsp;that order of Gopal Krishna&nbsp;Maharaj and Srila&nbsp;Prabhupad, then your devotional service is also successful.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Hare Krsna!&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>HH Gopal Krishna Maharaj&nbsp;Triobhav&nbsp;Utsav| HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj | April 14, 2026&nbsp; This is the second celebration of the disappearance of Gopal&nbsp;Krishna&nbsp;Maharaj. As everyone is aware, he has played&nbsp;a very important&nbsp;role in the expansion of ISKCON in India.&nbsp;In fact, we see that the whole of Delhi, which is a huge city, is covered with about [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-5344","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/5344","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}